'''抗体依赖增强作用'''（{{lang-en|Antibody-dependent enhancement}}，[[缩写|缩写]]：ADE）又称'''抗体依赖增强感染效应'''、'''抗体依赖性增强'''，是指一些次优的[[抗体|抗体]]（一般为可结合病毒的非[[中和抗体|中和抗体]]）与[[病毒|病毒]]结合后，不仅不能防止病毒侵入人体细胞，反而会增强病毒感染免疫细胞、促进病毒在体内的复制，恶化疾病的严重度或诱发更严重的额外徵候。<ref name="Tirado_2003">{{cite journal | vauthors = Tirado SM, Yoon KJ | title = Antibody-dependent enhancement of virus infection and disease | journal = Viral Immunology | volume = 16 | issue = 1 | pages = 69–86 | date = 2003 | pmid = 12725690 | doi = 10.1089/088282403763635465 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Kulkarni|first=Ruta|date=2019-11-05|title=Antibody-Dependent Enhancement of Viral Infections|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7119964/|journal=Dynamics of Immune Activation in Viral Diseases|pages=9–41|doi=10.1007/978-981-15-1045-8_2|pmc=7119964|access-date=2020-09-23|archive-date=2020-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207111224/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7119964/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==机制==
抗体依赖性增强的機制有兩種：

一為次优抗体与[[病毒|病毒]]结合后，其{{le|Fc段|Fragment crystallizable region}}再与免疫细胞表面表达的{{le|Fc受体|Fc receptor}}结合，接着使病毒進入免疫細胞，但病毒因抗體對抗原的結合力不佳而未被中和分解，反而在免疫細胞中複製增殖；此機制已在人類的[[登革熱|登革熱]]感染與貓的[[貓冠狀病毒|貓冠狀病毒]]感染中觀察到<ref name="pmid32908214"/>。例如：感染過登革熱的患者若再被另一亞型的登革熱病毒感染，會依之前的免疫記憶產生中和力較低的抗體，而可能發生抗体依赖增强感染的效應，這也是上述兩種疾病[[疫苗|疫苗]]開發困難的原因之一<ref name="pmid33194810">{{cite journal| author=Shukla R, Ramasamy V, Shanmugam RK, Ahuja R, Khanna N| title=Antibody-Dependent Enhancement: A Challenge for Developing a Safe Dengue Vaccine. | journal=Front Cell Infect Microbiol | year= 2020 | volume= 10 | issue=  | pages= 572681 | pmid=33194810 | doi=10.3389/fcimb.2020.572681 | pmc=7642463 | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=33194810  }} </ref>。

另一種機制則為次優抗體和抗原結合後，与[[补体|补体]]相互作用，接着促進[[發炎反應|發炎反應]]；例如[[人類呼吸道合胞病毒|人類呼吸道合胞病毒]]（RSV）與[[麻疹病毒|麻疹病毒]]感染時即可能在呼吸道組織發生抗体依赖性增强，激活數種[[細胞激素|細胞激素]]與[[補體|補體]]而造成發炎，嚴重者甚至可能導致[[急性呼吸窘迫症候群|急性呼吸窘迫症候群]]<ref name="pmid32908214"/>。

==引发之病毒种类==
除上述病毒（登革热病毒、貓冠狀病毒、人類呼吸道合胞病毒、麻疹病毒）外，有[[體外|體外]]實驗顯示[[人類免疫缺乏病毒|人類免疫缺乏病毒]]、[[伊波拉病毒|伊波拉病毒]]、[[流感病毒|流感病毒]]、{{tsl|en|黃熱病毒屬|Flavivirus|黃熱病毒}}與[[严重急性呼吸道综合征冠状病毒|SARS冠狀病毒]]<ref name="pmid31826992">{{cite journal| author=Wan Y, Shang J, Sun S, Tai W, Chen J, Geng Q | display-authors=etal| title=Molecular Mechanism for Antibody-Dependent Enhancement of Coronavirus Entry. | journal=J Virol | year= 2020 | volume= 94 | issue= 5 | pages=  | pmid=31826992 | doi=10.1128/JVI.02015-19 | pmc=7022351 | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=31826992  }} </ref><ref name="pmid21775467">{{cite journal| author=Jaume M, Yip MS, Cheung CY, Leung HL, Li PH, Kien F | display-authors=etal| title=Anti-severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus spike antibodies trigger infection of human immune cells via a pH- and cysteine protease-independent FcγR pathway. | journal=J Virol | year= 2011 | volume= 85 | issue= 20 | pages= 10582-97 | pmid=21775467 | doi=10.1128/JVI.00671-11 | pmc=3187504 | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=21775467  }} </ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Implications of antibody-dependent enhancement of infection for SARS-CoV-2 countermeasures|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41587-020-0577-1|last=Eroshenko|first=Nikolai|last2=Gill|first2=Taylor|date=2020-07|journal=Nature Biotechnology|issue=7|doi=10.1038/s41587-020-0577-1|volume=38|pages=789–791|language=en|issn=1546-1696|last3=Keaveney|first3=Marianna K.|last4=Church|first4=George M.|last5=Trevejo|first5=Jose M.|last6=Rajaniemi|first6=Hannu|access-date=2022-01-10|archive-date=2021-06-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210604220638/https://www.nature.com/articles/s41587-020-0577-1}}</ref>感染皆可能發生抗体依赖性增强<ref name="pmid32908214">{{cite journal| author=Lee WS, Wheatley AK, Kent SJ, DeKosky BJ| title=Antibody-dependent enhancement and SARS-CoV-2 vaccines and therapies. | journal=Nat Microbiol | year= 2020 | volume= 5 | issue= 10 | pages= 1185-1191 | pmid=32908214 | doi=10.1038/s41564-020-00789-5 | pmc= | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=32908214  }} </ref>。

2020年，[[2019冠状病毒病疫苗|2019冠状病毒病疫苗]]開發過程中曾在動物實驗發現抗体依赖性增强的現象，有[[反疫苗活動家|反疫苗活動家]]以此機制為拒絕施打疫苗的理由，但目前未知人體施打疫苗後是否會出現此現象<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Health Feedback |url=https://healthfeedback.org/claimreview/no-evidence-that-covid-19-vaccines-cause-more-severe-disease-antibody-dependent-enhancement-has-not-been-observed-in-clinical-trials/ |date=2020-11-27 |type=Fact check |title=No evidence that COVID-19 vaccines cause more severe disease; antibody-dependent enhancement has not been observed in clinical trials |editor=Teoh F |access-date=2021-04-29 |archive-date=2021-02-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210204065329/https://healthfeedback.org/claimreview/no-evidence-that-covid-19-vaccines-cause-more-severe-disease-antibody-dependent-enhancement-has-not-been-observed-in-clinical-trials/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=sbm>{{cite web |publisher=[[Science-Based_Medicine|Science-Based Medicine]] |author=Gorski DH |title=It was inevitable that antivaxxers would claim that COVID-19 vaccines make females infertile |url=https://sciencebasedmedicine.org/it-was-inevitable-that-antivaxxers-would-claim-that-covid-19-vaccines-make-females-infertile/ |date=2020-12-14 |quote=the overall petition ... spends far more verbiage on PCR, Sanger sequencing, and the not-unreasonable but thus far not observed concern about antibody-dependent enhancement (ADE) due to a vaccine |access-date=2021-04-29 |archive-date=2021-02-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210209003222/https://sciencebasedmedicine.org/it-was-inevitable-that-antivaxxers-would-claim-that-covid-19-vaccines-make-females-infertile/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

